  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN138.1-kilavi">talaimakaṉ ciṟaippuṟattāṉākat talaimakaḷ <app><lem>tōḻikkuc</lem><rdg wit="#C2 #C3 #C7 #RK">tōḻikkuc colluvāḷāyt talaimakaḷ</rdg></app> colliyatu.</p> 
          <p xml:lang="en">What SHE said to the confidante when HE was behind the fence.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN138.1">
              <l>ikuḷai kēṭṭiciṟ kātalan tōḻi</l>
              <l>kuvaḷai yuṇkaṇ ṭeṇpaṉi malka</l>
              <l>vaṟitiyāṉ varuntiya cellaṟ kaṉṉai</l>
              <l>piṟitoṉ<supplied>ṟu</supplied> kaṭuttaṉa ḷāki vēmpiṉ</l>
              <l>veṟikoḷ pācilai nīlamoṭu cūṭi</l>
              <l>yuṭalu<supplied>na</supplied>rk kaṭanta kaṭalan tāṉait</l>
              <l>tiruntilai neṭuvēṟ ṟeṉṉavaṉ potiyi</l>
              <l><supplied>la</supplied>ruñcimai yiḻitaru mārttuvara laruviyiṟ</l>
              <l>ṟatumpucī riṉṉiyaṅ kaṟaṅkak kaitoḻu</l>
              <l>turukeḻu ciṟappiṉ murukumaṉait tarīik</l>
              <l>kaṭampu<del>tu</del>ṅ kaḷiṟum pāṭi nuṭaṅkupu</l>
              <l>tōṭun toṭalaiyuṅ kaikkoṇ ṭalkalum</l>
              <l>pāṭiṉa ḷāta ṉaṉṟō nīṭu</l>
              <l>niṉṉoṭu teḷitta naṉmalai nāṭaṉ</l>
              <l>kuṟivara laraināṭ kuṉṟat tucci</l>
              <l>neṟikeṭa vīḻn<supplied>ta</supplied> tuṉṉaruṅ kūriruṭ</l>
              <l>ṭirumaṇi yumiḻnta nākaṅ kāntaṭ</l>
              <l>koḻumaṭaṟ putuppū vūtun tumpi<anchor n="1"></anchor></l>
              <l>naṉṉiṟa maruḷu maruviṭa</l>
              <l>riṉṉā nīḷiṭai niṉaiyumeṉ ṉeñcē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>Companion, listen, beloved friend: (1)</l>
                <l>that mother, because of the distress suffered by me, poorly, (3)</l>
                <l>so that clear dew increases in [my] waterlily kajal eyes, (2)</l>
                <l>being in doubt whether something else [is the cause] (4a-c)</l>
                <l>should have worn perfumed green leaves of neem with blue lotus (4d-5)</l>
                <l>[and folded her] hands in worship, while sweet instruments sounded in resounding melodies, (9)</l>
                <l>like the waterfalls coming noisily as they tumble from the difficult[-to-reach] summit (8)</l>
                <l>of the southern [king’s mount] Potiyil, long spear with perfect blade (7)</l> 
                <l>[and] an ocean[-like] army that overcame those who oppose [him], (6)</l>
                <l>giving a house to Murukaṉ of beautiful/fearful superiority, (10)</l>
                <l>singing of [his] Kadamba trees and elephant, swaying [with the rhythm], (11)</l>
                <l>holding in [her] hands palm fronds and a wreath, (12a-c)</l>
                <l>[that she] should have sung all night, [is] that good? (12d-13a-c)</l>
                <l>My heart thinks of the unpleasant long way (20)</l>
                <l>with difficult clefts, (19d)</l>
                <l>where the man from a land of good mountains who had long been informed by you (13d-14)</l>
                <l rend="indent4">confuses the good colour (19ab)</l>
                <l>of bees that fill themselves on the rich-leaved new flowers (18)</l>
                <l>of the Malabar lilies with the snakes that have spit up brilliant gems (17)</l>
                <l>in the ample darkness difficult to approach that descended, for the paths to get lost, (16)</l>
                <l>onto the peaks of the hills at midnight, when coming for [our] tryst. (15)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>

